olive oil
1 carrot
½ cucumber
½ fresh chilli  (optional)
1 packet teriyaki sauce
1 tbs brown sugar
2 tsp vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
1 packet beef mince
½ sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 egg
¼ tsp salt
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet ginger paste
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet coriander

• Grate carrot. Thinly slice cucumber(see ingredients) into half-moons.
Thinly slice fresh chilli (if using).
• In a small bowl, combine teriyaki sauce, the brown sugar, vinegar and
a splash of water. Set aside.
• In a medium bowl, combine beef mince, sweet soy seasoning,
fine breadcrumbs, the egg, salt and a pinch of pepper.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of the beef mixture into small meatballs (4-5 per person). Transfer to a plate.

Little cooks: Join the fun by helping combine the ingredients and shaping the mixture into meatballs!

• In a large frying pan, heat a generous drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook meatballs, turning, until browned and cooked through,
8-10 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded!).
• Add ginger paste, then cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add teriyaki sauce mixture, then cook, tossing, until meatballs are well
coated, 1-2 minutes.

• While the meatballs are cooking, in a large bowl, combine garlic aioli and a drizzle of vinegar.
• Add shredded cabbage mix, carrot and cucumber. Toss to coat and season to taste with salt and pepper.

• Divide Asian slaw between bowls.
• Top with teriyaki beef meatballs, spooning over any remaining glaze.
• Tear over coriander and sprinkle over chilli to serve. Enjoy!